{
  "texts": [
    "Option 1 is used mainly for RAN capability exposure and thus at least one RAN capability exposure service must be defined so that the core network NF (such as NWDAF) can directly invoke this service to obtain the information about RANs.",
    "Option 2 is essential for direct service invocation between the RAN NF and core network NF, and the traditional nonaccess stratum (NAS) model needs to be changed.",
    "In other words, the dependency relationship between NAS signaling must be determined.",
    "The solution in the first stage can empower several scenarios; however, the solution in the second stage can truly realize the value of service-based architecture.",
    "In the second stage, the decoupling of RAN functionalities into services as well as the integration of RAN and core network (CN) services and procedures must be considered to better meet the design principles of high cohesion and low coupling."
  ]
}